Key genes include various interleukins (IL-1, IL-6, IL-10), TNF receptors, and transforming growth factor beta (TGF-β) receptors, all of which facilitate communication between immune cells and contribute to processes like cell differentiation, apoptosis, and tissue repair. Research findings emphasize the significance of these pathways in diverse contexts, such as spinal cord ependymoma and T. gondii infection, where cytokine signaling modulates immune responses and influences disease progression. Overall, the convergence of these signaling pathways underscores their collective impact on maintaining homeostasis and modulating inflammation. NA 0.92
